data.name: Miso Glazed Black Cod with Sautéed Bok Choy
data.quickTastyDescription: Delicately sweet and savory black cod paired with vibrant bok choy, perfect for a healthy gourmet meal.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a small bowl, mix miso paste, mirin, soy sauce, and brown sugar until smooth.
Marinate the black cod fillets in the miso mixture for at least 15 minutes.
Place the fillets on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper and bake for 15-20 minutes, or until the fish is flaky and cooked through.
While the fish is cooking, heat sesame oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add minced garlic and sauté for about 30 seconds until fragrant.
Add bok choy and stir-fry for 4-5 minutes until tender but still vibrant in color.
Serve the miso glazed black cod over the sautéed bok choy, garnishing with chopped green onions and sesame seeds.
